item.title: Experience CODERS only
item.dc:creator: @hmpph hmpph
item.description:
@hmpph wrote:

Just change the starting co-ords to the co-ords that you want to start at.

So if its something like this.

EXAMPLE 1;

teleportToX = 1234;
teleportToY = 1234;

Change it to:

EXAMPLE 2;

teleportToX = 1234;
teleportToY = 5678;

Then compile and run.
You should then start at the co-ords:

X= 1234
Y= 5678

^^These are just examples though so you can use any X and Y co-ord that you like.

There should also be a “Co-ords” list somewhere in your source, so that can be helpful for quick reference.

I hope thats what you mean BTW lol, if not just PM me and I’ll see if i can help ya.
Okey,

Hmpph
